Fields.Name: ACEN
Fields.Documentation: Selects the trim value to use for the IPO. The reset default for this field uses the factory trim for the IPO. Setting this field to 1 uses the automatic calibration trim output stored in FCR_AUTOCAL0.ldtrm.

Enum.Name: DIS
Enum.Description: Use Default Trim from the Factory.
Enum.Documentation: Use Default Trim from the Factory..

Enum.Name: EN
Enum.Documentation: Use Automatic Calibration Trim Value..

Enum.Name: NOT
Enum.Documentation: Not Running.

Enum.Name: RUN
Enum.Documentation: Running.

Fields.Name: LDTRM
Fields.Documentation: Set this bit to load the initial trim value for the IPO from FCR_AUTOCAL1.inittrm. This bit is cleared by hardware once the load is complete.

Fields.Name: GAININV
Fields.Documentation: Set this field to invert the up/down trim steps during calibration operations.

Enum.Name: NOT
Enum.Documentation: Trim Steps are Not Inverted..

Enum.Name: RUN
Enum.Description: Enable Inverted Trim Steps for Calibration.
Enum.Documentation: Enable Inverted Trim Steps for Calibration..

Fields.Name: ATOMIC
Fields.Documentation: Set this bit to start an automatic atomic calibration of the IPO. The calibration runs for FCR_AUTOCAL2.donecnt milliseconds. This bit is automatically cleared by hardware when the calibration is complete.

Enum.Name: NOT
Enum.Documentation: Not Running.

Enum.Name: RUN
Enum.Documentation: Running.

Fields.Name: MU
Fields.Documentation: Load this field with the desired number of trim adjustment pulses required before the trim is updated during automatic calibration operation.

Fields.Name: HIRC96MACTMROUT
Fields.Documentation: This field contains the calculated trim output from an automatic calibration run.

Fields.Name: INITTRM
Fields.Description: IPO Trim Automatic Calibration Initial Trim
Fields.Documentation: This field contains the initial trim setting for the IPO. Set this field to the desired initial trim value to use for an IPO automatic calibration operation. The closer this field is to the target trim value required, the faster the automatic trim operation completes.

Fields.Name: DONECNT
Fields.Description: IPO Trim Automatic Calibration Run Time
Fields.Documentation: Set this field to the desired number of milliseconds for the atomic calibration run time for the IPO.

Fields.Name: ACDIV
Fields.Description: IPO Trim Automatic Calibration Divide Factor
Fields.Documentation: The target frequency of the calibration is determined by dividing the IPO frequency by 32,768 before comparing it with the ERTCO frequency. For example, to achieve a target IPO frequency of 120MHz, load this field with 0xE4E (3,662).

Fields.Name: RDSGCSEL
Fields.Documentation: This field is the gray code setting used when the FCR_FCTRL0.rdsgcset is set to 1.

Fields.Name: RDSGCSET
Fields.Documentation: Setting this field to 1 enables software control of the HyperBus RDS gray code selection.

Fields.Name: HYPERCGDLY
Fields.Documentation: This field controls the HyperBus clock generator delay.

Fields.Name: USBCLKSEL
Fields.Documentation: This field selects the clock source for the USB peripheral.

Fields.Name: MODE
Fields.Documentation: This two bit field selects the current operating mode for the device. Note that code execution only occurs during ACTIVE mode.

Enum.Name: ACTIVE
Enum.Documentation: Active Mode.

Enum.Name: SLEEP
Enum.Documentation: Cortex-M4 Active, RISC-V Sleep Mode.

Enum.Name: STANDBY
Enum.Documentation: Standby Mode.

Enum.Name: BACKUP
Enum.Documentation: Backup Mode.

Enum.Name: LPM
Enum.Description: LPM or CM4 Deep Sleep Mode
Enum.Documentation: LPM or CM4 Deep Sleep Mode.

Enum.Name: UPM
Enum.Documentation: UPM.

Enum.Name: POWERDOWN
Enum.Documentation: Power Down Mode.

Fields.Name: GPIO_WE
Fields.Documentation: This bit enables all GPIO pins as potential wakeup sources. Any GPIO configured for wakeup is capable of causing an exit from IDLE or STANDBY modes when this bit is set.

Enum.Name: DIS
Enum.Documentation: Wake up Disable.

Enum.Name: EN
Enum.Documentation: Wake up Enable.

Fields.Name: RTC_WE
Fields.Documentation: This bit enables RTC alarm as wakeup source. If enabled, the desired RTC alarm must be configured via the RTC control registers.

Enum.Name: DIS
Enum.Documentation: Wake up Disable.

Enum.Name: EN
Enum.Documentation: Wake up Enable.

Fields.Name: USB_WE
Fields.Documentation: This bit enables USB IRQ as wakeup source

Enum.Name: DIS
Enum.Documentation: Wake up Disable.

Enum.Name: EN
Enum.Documentation: Wake up Enable.

Fields.Name: WUT_WE
Fields.Documentation: This bit enables the Wake-Up Timer as wakeup source.

Enum.Name: DIS
Enum.Documentation: Wake up Disable.

Enum.Name: EN
Enum.Documentation: Wake up Enable.

Fields.Name: AINCOMP_WE
Fields.Documentation: This bit enables AIN COMP as wakeup source.

Enum.Name: DIS
Enum.Documentation: Wake up Disable.

Enum.Name: EN
Enum.Documentation: Wake up Enable.

Fields.Name: ISO_PD
Fields.Documentation: This bit selects the ISO clock power state in DEEPSLEEP mode.

Enum.Name: ACTIVE
Enum.Documentation: Mode is Active.

Enum.Name: DEEPSLEEP
Enum.Documentation: Powered Down in DEEPSLEEP.

Fields.Name: IPO_PD
Fields.Documentation: This bit selects IPO clock power state in DEEPSLEEP mode.

Enum.Name: ACTIVE
Enum.Documentation: Mode is Active.

Enum.Name: DEEPSLEEP
Enum.Documentation: Powered Down in DEEPSLEEP.

Fields.Name: IBRO_PD
Fields.Documentation: This bit selects 7.3725 MHz clock power state in DEEPSLEEP mode.

Enum.Name: ACTIVE
Enum.Documentation: Mode is Active.

Enum.Name: DEEPSLEEP
Enum.Documentation: Powered Down in DEEPSLEEP.

Fields.Name: ERFO_BP
Fields.Documentation: This bit is set to 0 on a POR is not affected by other forms of reset. Set this field to 1 to use a square wave input as the clock source for the ERFO driving the HFXIN pin.

Fields.Name: BSTAPEN
Fields.Documentation: This field's reset value matches GCR_SYSST.icelock. Do not modify.

Fields.Name: FLASH_PAGE_FLIP
Fields.Documentation: This field flips the bottom and top halves of flash memory. This bit is controlled by hardware and should not be modified by software.

Enum.Name: NOT_FLIPPED
Enum.Documentation: Physical layout matches logical layout.

Enum.Name: FLIPPED
Enum.Documentation: Top and bottom halves flipped.

Fields.Name: ICC0_FLUSH
Fields.Documentation: Write 1 to flush the code cache and the instruction buffer for the CM4 (CPU0). This bit is automatically cleared to 0 when the flush is complete. Writing 0 has no effect and does not stop a cache flush in progress.

Enum.Name: COMPLETE
Enum.Documentation: ICC0 flush complete.

Enum.Name: FLUSH
Enum.Documentation: Flush the contents of the ICC0 cache.

Fields.Name: SRCC_FLUSH
Fields.Documentation: Set this field to 1 to flush the SRCC.

Enum.Name: ENABLED
Enum.Documentation: SPIXR (SRCC) Cache is Enabled

Enum.Name: DISABLED
Enum.Documentation: SPIXR (SRCC) Cache is Disabled

Fields.Name: SYSCACHE_DIS
Fields.Documentation: Set this field to 1 to disable the EMCC.

Enum.Name: ENABLED
Enum.Documentation: EMCC enabled.

Enum.Name: DISABLED
Enum.Documentation: EMCC disabled.

Fields.Name: CCHK
Fields.Documentation: This bit is self-clearing when the ROM checksum calculation is complete, and the result is available at bit GCR_SYSCTRL.chkres. Writing a 0 has no effect.

Enum.Name: NOOP
Enum.Documentation: No operation.

Enum.Name: START
Enum.Documentation: Start ROM checksum calculation.

Fields.Name: SWD_DIS
Fields.Documentation: This bit is used to disable the serial wire debug interface.

Fields.Name: CHKRES
Fields.Documentation: This field is the result after setting the bit GCR_SYSCTRL.cchk. This field is only valid after the ROM checksum is complete and GCR_SYSCTRL.cchk is cleared by the hardware.

Enum.Name: PASS
Enum.Documentation: ROM checksum calculation passed.

Enum.Name: FAIL
Enum.Documentation: ROM checksum calculation failed.

Fields.Name: OVR
Fields.Documentation: This field must be set to 0b10 for proper device operation.

Registers.Documentation: Each bit controls the GPIO_EN setting for one GPIO pin on the associated port. These bits configure the corresponding device pin for digital I/O or an alternate function mode. The fields can be modified directly by writing to this register or indirectly through GPIOn_EN0_SET or GPIOn_EN0_CLR.

Registers.Documentation: Each bit controls the GPIO_EN setting for one GPIO pin on the associated port. These bits configure the corresponding device pin for digital I/O or an alternate function mode. The fields can be modified directly by writing to this register or indirectly through GPIOn_EN0_SET or GPIOn_EN0_CLR.

Registers.Documentation: Each bit controls the GPIO_EN setting for one GPIO pin on the associated port. These bits configure the corresponding device pin for digital I/O or an alternate function mode. The fields can be modified directly by writing to this register or indirectly through GPIOn_EN0_SET or GPIOn_EN0_CLR.

Registers.Documentation: Each bit controls the GPIO_EN setting for one GPIO pin on the associated port. These bits configure the corresponding device pin for digital I/O or an alternate function mode. The fields can be modified directly by writing to this register or indirectly through GPIOn_EN0_SET or GPIOn_EN0_CLR.
